title: 'Imminent danger of death' for about 400 people on boat between Greece and Malta
description: A boat carrying about 400 people "in distress" has been spotted adrift between Greece and Malta and is taking on water, support services have said.

title: Eight people missing after explosion and collapse of two buildings in Marseille
description: Eight people are feared to be trapped under the rubble of two buildings that collapsed following an explosion in the south of France.

title: British woman in critical condition after fall from sixth-floor hotel balcony in Benidorm
description: A British woman is in a critical condition in hospital after falling from a sixth-floor hotel balcony in Benidorm.

title: 'A shell exploded and shrapnel hit my face': An injured Ukrainian's journey from the war to Dublin
description: After one year of fighting, no one holds any illusions about the war in Ukraine.

title: Injured Tiger Woods withdraws from The Masters after 'struggling to walk'
description: Tiger Woods has withdrawn from The Masters due to injury.

title: Father of killed British-Israeli sisters asks 'how will I explain to their mother what has happened?'
description: The father of two British-Israeli sisters shot dead in the occupied West Bank has broken down at their funeral as he paid tribute to his "beautiful angels" while their grief-stricken siblings sobbed as they clutched their bodies.

title: 'Hazard' warning in Hamburg as cloud with possible 'chemical components' drifts towards city centre
description: Hamburg's fire brigade has issued a "hazard" warning as a cloud possibly containing "chemical components" drifts towards the city centre.

title: China and Taiwan ships in stand-off near sensitive buffer zone
description: About 20 military ships - half from China and half from Taiwan - are involved in a stand-off near the Taiwan Strait's sensitive median line, according to Reuters.

title: Saudi delegation arrives in Yemen to negotiate permanent ceasefire with Houthi rebels
description: Saudi officials are in Yemen's capital for peace talks it is hoped could end the country's eight year conflict.

title: At least 44 killed in 'despicable and barbaric' attacks in Burkina Faso
description: At least 44 people have been killed by Islamic extremists in attacks in northern Burkina Faso, the government has said.

title: Israel retaliates after six missiles fired from Syria towards Golan Heights
description: Six rockets have been fired from Syria towards Israel overnight, according to the Israeli military.

title: Last surviving Nuremberg trials prosecutor dies aged 103
description: Ben Ferencz, the last surviving prosecutor from the Nuremberg trials in Germany, has died at the age of 103.
